EMERGENCY LANDING
Remain calm and follow the instructions of your crew
at all times.
Loosen your collar and tie, remove glasses, hats, sharp
objects from clothing or
pockets,
and
take off your
shoes. (Take shoes with you when leaving the aircraft).
Do not remove any other clothing.
Put your seat in an upright position, fasten your seat
belt securely around your hips, and place both feet
together flat on the floor. Lean over, cross your arms,
hold your knees, and press your head into your folded
arms. Remain in this position until the aircraft comes to
a complete stop. (One or more impacts may follow the
initial impact).
Follow the crew's instructions when you leave the air-
craft.
RADIO RECEIVERS
Radio receivers may not be operated while the aircraft is in
flight. They may act as miniature broadcasting stations and interfere with the aircraft's
navigation system, causing incorrect readings. Should you wish to operate any other elec-
tronic device, please notify the stewardess.
TRANS-PROVINCIAL
